The article discusses the Reforming American Immigration for a Strong Economy (RAISE) Act, which aims to create a merit-based immigration system in the United States. The article highlights that low-skilled and unskilled immigration has increased over the years, leading to decreased wages and harm to vulnerable citizens. The RAISE Act is supported by President Donald J. Trump and aims to prioritize immigrants based on their skills, while also protecting American workers' jobs. The Act is seen as a fulfillment of President Trump's promise to reform the immigration system to prioritize American interests.